ore social justice and equality through education.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEducation, Bilingual. 0aLinguistic minoritiesxEducation. 0aMinoritiesxEducation. 0aMulticultural education. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aAikio-Puoskari, Ulla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBenson, Carol, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCummins, Jim, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGarcía, Ofelia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeugh, Kathleen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHough, David A., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobsen Pérez, Susanne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJhingran, Dhir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMagar, Ram Bahadur Thapa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcCarty, Teresa L., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMishra, Mahendra Kumar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohanty, Ajit K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMohanty, Ajit K., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aNicholas, Andrea Bear, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanda, Minati, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPanda, Minati, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPhillipson, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPhillipson, Robert, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRamesh, Gumidyala, econtributor.4